  "why": "DeepStellar’s testing component (Coverage-Guided Testing, CGT) and its adversarial-detection design assume semantic consistency and naturalness: they use metamorphic mutation operators and conservative (small) perturbation parameters so mutants remain realistic and preserve human-perceived meaning. However, the paper describes an iterative queue-based mutation loop that accepts and re-queues mutants that increase coverage (Algorithm 2) without any explicit mechanism that constrains cumulative distortion relative to the original seed (e.g., bounding total distance to the original seed or fixing semantically critical content across iterations). Thus plausibility/naturalness and semantic consistency are enforced at the per-mutation / successive-step level (via conservative, metamorphic mutations), but the design does not explicitly prevent drift from accumulating across multiple mutation iterations.",
